"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909099","Home Office","false","2018-05-25","<p>The EU Settlement Scheme is being designed with users in mind, and we are engaging with stakeholders who represent EU citizens in the UK to discuss and understand their needs. Our regular stakeholder groups include community representatives, employers, the EU27 consulates, and organisations representing vulnerable groups. We are developing a streamlined, user-friendly, digital application system, with multiple service options to meet the needs of a varied customer base, including additional support for the vulnerable.</p><p>We have launched a targeted communications campaign to maximise awareness and reassure EU citizens of our commitment to protect their rights and entitlements. Activity will increase as we approach the launch of the scheme before the end of this year.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","146060 ; 146061 ; 146062 ; 146064 ; 146065 ; 146066","2018-05-25T13:54:07.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909099/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909099/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909099/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-21","Immigration: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that the new process for applying for settled status for EU citizens resident in the UK is user-friendly for applicants who have English as a second language.","false","Biography information for Ms Diane Abbott","Hackney North and Stoke Newington","Ms Diane Abbott","146063"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909100","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-06-01","<p>Following the publication of the Government response to the Internet Safety Strategy Green Paper on 20 May, DCMS and Home Office will jointly work on a White Paper with other government departments, to be published later this year. This will set out legislation to be brought forward that tackles a range of both legal and illegal harms, from cyberbullying to online child sexual exploitation. The Government will continue to collaborate closely with industry on this work, to ensure it builds on progress already made.</p><p> </p><p>As the Prime Minister said in her speech at Davos on 25 January, we are looking at the legal liability that social media companies have for the illegal content shared on their sites. Before taking any decisions we will be working closely with the full range of stakeholders who have an interest in this area.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-06-01T10:39:28.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909100/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909100/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909100/answer",,,,,,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-05-21","Social Media: Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what recent steps his Department has taken to help tackle illegal behaviour on social media platforms.","false","Biography information for Ben Bradley","Mansfield","Ben Bradley","146345"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909101","Home Office","false","2018-05-25","<p>The EU Settlement Scheme is being designed with users in mind, and we are engaging with stakeholders who represent EU citizens in the UK to discuss and understand their needs. Our regular stakeholder groups include community representatives, employers, the EU27 consulates, and organisations representing vulnerable groups. We are developing a streamlined, user-friendly, digital application system, with multiple service options to meet the needs of a varied customer base, including additional support for the vulnerable.</p><p>We have launched a targeted communications campaign to maximise awareness and reassure EU citizens of our commitment to protect their rights and entitlements. Activity will increase as we approach the launch of the scheme before the end of this year.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","146060 ; 146061 ; 146062 ; 146063 ; 146065 ; 146066","2018-05-25T13:54:07.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909101/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909101/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909101/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-21","Immigration: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, by what means his Department will convey information to EU citizens resident in the UK on when they need to apply for settled status.","false","Biography information for Ms Diane Abbott","Hackney North and Stoke Newington","Ms Diane Abbott","146064"
