"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909169","Department for International Trade","false","2018-05-24","<p>I have agreed a number of joint statements with partner countries setting out our mutual ambition to ensure continuity of trading relations as the UK leaves the EU, and have already published these as they have been agreed. In July 2017, my noble Friend, the then Minister of State for Trade Policy (Lord Price) agreed such a statement of intent with ministers from the Southern African Customs Union. In November 2017, I agreed a similar statement with the CARIFORUM trade ministers and representatives, and also with the East and Southern Africa States in April 2018.</p><p>More information can be found in the following links: <a href="http://www.sacu.int/docs/pr/2017/pr0719.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.sacu.int/docs/pr/2017/pr0719.pdf</a></p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/joint-statement-on-trade-between-uk-and-the-cariforum-states" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/news/joint-statement-on-trade-between-uk-and-the-cariforum-states</a></p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/joint-statement-on-trade-between-uk-and-the-esa-states" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/news/joint-statement-on-trade-between-uk-and-the-esa-states</a></p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","146047 ; 146048","2018-05-24T13:10:00.43Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909169/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909169/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909169/answer",,,,,,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-05-21","Overseas Trade","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, pursuant to his oral contribution by the Minister for Trade Policy of 17 May 2018, Official Report, column 410, if he will publish the Memorandum of Understanding between the UK and the Eastern and Southern Africa EPA Group.","false","Biography information for Barry Gardiner","Brent North","Barry Gardiner","146049"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909170","Department for International Trade","false","2018-05-25","<p>We are committed to scrutiny and engagement that is inclusive, meaningful and transparent, whilst ensuring that we do not undermine or prejudice our negotiating position.</p><p>In line with diplomatic practices, it would not be appropriate to take unilateral decisions on disclosing information on engagements with our trading partners. Individual announcements and statements will continue to be made available on the department’s website.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2018-05-25T11:11:22.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909170/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909170/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909170/answer","Chelsea and Fulham","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909170/answer/previousversion/60241","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909170/answer/previousversion/60241","Biography information for Greg Hands","202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-05-21","Trade Agreements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, if he will publish any documents pertaining to agreements reached by the Trade and Investment Working Groups.","false","Biography information for Barry Gardiner","Brent North","Barry Gardiner","146050"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909171","Home Office","false","2018-05-30","<p>Section 58 of the Act commits the Secretary of State to review the operation of the Act, prepare a report of the review, and lay a copy of the report before Parliament 30 months after the commencement of the Act. The 30 month review of the Psychoactive Substances Act 2016 will be published in November 2018.</p><p>Early evidence since the Psychoactive Substances Act 2016 (2016 PSA) came into effect shows that it is working. It has removed psychoactive substances from open sale.</p><p>Since the Act came into force, over 300 retailers across the United Kingdom have either closed down or are no longer selling psychoactive substances, police have arrested suppliers and action by the National Crime Agency has resulted in the removal of these drugs for sale on UK based websites.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2018-05-30T13:08:44.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909171/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909171/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909171/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-21","Drugs: Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent assessment he has made of progress in tackling the production and distribution of illegal psychoactive substances.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Nigel Dodds","146127"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909172","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-05-25","<p>We are organising two separate roundtable discussions with both leaseholders and industry which will take place shortly.</p><p>9 private owners of leasehold properties, the Leasehold Advisory Service (LEASE), the Leasehold Knowledge Partnership, the National Fire Chiefs Council and the Homeowners Alliance have been invited to the leaseholder roundtable.</p><p>Invitations to the industry roundtable are being finalised.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2018-05-25T14:39:05.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909172/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909172/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/909172/answer",,,,,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-05-21","High Rise Flats: Fire Prevention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, which companies and organisations have been invited to attend the proposed roundtable discussion on the removal and replacement of cladding on privately owned tower blocks.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","146109"
