"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/907143","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-05-23","<p>We have interpreted your questions to be about Access to Work workplace assessments.</p><p> </p><p>The data requested are not held centrally and to provide them would incur disproportionate cost.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","145583 ; 145584","2018-05-23T15:06:05.06Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/907143/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/907143/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/907143/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-05-18","Hyperactivity: Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the number of workplace assessments in Scotland for attention deficit hyperactivity disorder in each year since 2015.","false","Biography information for Martin Docherty-Hughes","West Dunbartonshire","Martin Docherty-Hughes","145582"
